  "body": "# submission name:\nqpose14_r55_segactions_minp\n\n# upload zipped `archive.zip`\n[archive.zip](https://github.com/EthanYangTW/comma_video_compression_challenge/releases/download/qpose14-r55-segactions-minp/archive.zip)\n\nSHA-256: `cc1dfa346811dade15044910fa0143e73a7a049b98aeec39b96a53481a0788bd`\n\n# report.txt\n```\n=== Evaluation config ===\n  batch_size: 16\n  device: cuda\n  num_threads: 2\n  prefetch_queue_depth: 4\n  report: submissions/qpose14_r55_segactions_minp/report.txt\n  seed: 1234\n  submission_dir: submissions/qpose14_r55_segactions_minp\n  uncompressed_dir: /root/comma_video_compression_challenge/videos\n  video_names_file: /root/comma_video_compression_challenge/public_test_video_names.txt\n=== Evaluation results over 600 samples ===\n  Average PoseNet Distortion: 0.00048653\n  Average SegNet Distortion: 0.00060686\n  Submission file size: 276,741 bytes\n  Original uncompressed size: 37,545,489 bytes\n  Compression Rate: 0.00737081\n  Final score: 100*segnet_dist + √(10*posenet_dist) + 25*rate = 0.31\n```\n\n# does your submission require gpu for evaluation (inflation)?\nyes\n\n# did you include the compression script? and want it to be merged?\nno\n\n# additional comments\nUpdated from the previous r55 payload to the `qpose14_r55_segactions_minp` payload with embedded SegNet tile-action corrections and fixed no-header single-blob packing. The archive is hosted as a release asset instead of being committed to the PR.\n",
